  <header class="main-hd">
    <h3 class="title">
      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/7120217/" class="title-link">关于美的沉思</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-7120217"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/yican/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u2129048-3.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/yican/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">红皇后</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2014-10-06"
      class="main-meta">2014-10-06 10:47:07</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_7120217_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                  最近陆续看了《审丑》与《美的沉思》，才发现我们曾经多么忽略近在身边的各种美与丑。 一本书的装帧设计、一幅画为我们展现的笔法，甚至是一张椅子的弧线或者某个建筑的造型，其实都有其美或者不美的特性。而这些也许是平时我们会经常忽略的。而这两本书恰恰从相反的方向上向我...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/7120217/#comments">(12回应)</a>
                  <div class="more-info pl clearfix">
                    <span class="left">12有用 / 1没用</span>
                  </div>
            </div>
